{{setTitle     "Get Started"}}
{{setSubTitle  "Quickstart your next web project."}}
{{setActiveNav "start"}}
{{setLoadYUI   true}}
{{addLocalCSS  "/css/start.css"}}
{{addLocalJS   "/js/start.js"}}


{{> header}}

<div class="content">
    {{sectionHeading "Step 1: Add Pure to your page"}}

    <p>
        You can add Pure to your page via Yahoo's CDN. Just add this {{code "<link>"}} tag to your {{code "<head>"}}, before your application styles.
    </p>

    {{#code wrap=true}}
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://yui.yahooapis.com/pure/{{pure.version}}/pure-min.css">
    {{/code}}

    <p>
        Alternatively, you can download Pure through Bower, or <a href="/customize/">check out other CDNs</a> that host Pure.
    </p>

    {{#code wrap=true}}
        bower install pure --save
    {{/code}}


    {{sectionHeading "Step 2: Customize your Pure Grid"}}
    <p>
        Pure ships with a 24-column grid system, but we don't include media queries since they can't be overridden by your website's styles. Instead, you can generate your own mobile-first responsive grid system by telling us a bit more about your site.
    </p>


    {{> start/grid-input-view}}

    <div class="grid-output"></div>
</div>
